HW3 - Named Entity Recognition with BiLSTM
============================================

Requirements: Python 3.8+, PyTorch, NumPy

Main notebook: HW3-CSCI544.ipynb (run all cells sequentially)

Task 1 - Simple BiLSTM
-----------------------
Train:
    python blstm1.py --mode train --data data

Predict (from saved model):
    python blstm1.py --mode predict --data data

Outputs: dev1.out, test1.out, blstm1.pt

Hyperparameters: lr=0.15, momentum=0.9, batch_size=32, epochs=30,
                 StepLR(step=7, gamma=0.5), grad_clip=5.0

Task 2 - BiLSTM with GloVe + Case Features
-------------------------------------------
Train:
    python blstm2.py --mode train --data data --glove glove.6B.100d

Predict (from saved model):
    python blstm2.py --mode predict --data data

Outputs: dev2.out, test2.out, blstm2.pt

Hyperparameters: emb_lr=0.001, other_lr=0.1, momentum=0.9, batch_size=32,
                 epochs=50, StepLR(step=10, gamma=0.5), grad_clip=5.0,
                 case_embedding_dim=10, n_case_categories=6

Case sensitivity strategy:
    GloVe is case-insensitive so all words are looked up by their
    lowercase form. To preserve case information, each word gets a
    categorical case feature (lowercase / UPPERCASE / Titlecase /
    has_digit / other) mapped through a learned 10-dim embedding.
    This is concatenated with the 100-dim word embedding before
    feeding into the BiLSTM (input dim = 110).

Bonus - BiLSTM-CNN
------------------
Included in the notebook. Adds a character-level CNN (char_emb=30,
Conv1d with 50 filters, kernel=3) to the Task 2 model.
Output: pred

Evaluation
----------
Copy conll03eval to the HW3 root directory first:
    cp eval/conll03eval .

Then run:
    python eval/eval.py -p dev1.out -g data/dev
    python eval/eval.py -p dev2.out -g data/dev
